Subject: [PATCH 1035/2241] apn806: dts: add revision info node

A8k A0 requires workaround for SATA.
This node will be used by SATA driver to distinguish
A0 and A1 revisions.

Important notice:
- When A8k A0 becomes unsupported - This commit should be
  removed!
- Don't submit this patch upstream

Change-Id: I57a7a4b26a2b848634a79d0fb2c2774512e5b56c
Signed-off-by: Igal Liberman <igall@marvell.com>
Reviewed-on: http://vgitil04.il.marvell.com:8080/33478
Reviewed-by: Wilson Ding <dingwei@marvell.com>
Reviewed-by: Omri Itach <omrii@marvell.com>
Tested-by: Omri Itach <omrii@marvell.com>
---
 arch/arm64/boot/dts/marvell/armada-ap806.dtsi | 5 +++++
 1 file changed, 5 insertions(+)

diff --git a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/marvell/armada-ap806.dtsi b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/marvell/armada-ap806.dtsi
index d17c477..702e390 100644
--- a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/marvell/armada-ap806.dtsi
+++ b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/marvell/armada-ap806.dtsi
@@ -367,6 +367,11 @@
 				reg = <0xF000 0x1000>;
 				interrupts = <GIC_SPI 18 IRQ_TYPE_LEVEL_HIGH>;
 			};
+
+			revision-info@610fcc {
+				compatible = "marvell,ap806-rev-info";
+				reg = <0x610FCC 0x4>;
+			};
 		};
 	};
 
